You’re absolutely right — GDP alone is a flawed metric when it comes to measuring true national progress. It’s easy to get lost in numbers, but what matters is how that wealth is distributed, how it improves lives, and how it fuels sustainable growth. Japan’s post-war recovery is a testament to resilience, innovation, and focus — lessons India can’t afford to ignore. Let’s stop celebrating hollow wins and start building real value.